South African graphic designer and illustrator Karabo Moletsane recently announced that she had collaborated with Nike. JOHANNESBURG - South African illustrator and artist Karabo Poppy Moletsane has collaborated with Nike By You to design the latest collection of Air Force1. Molestane announced the exciting news on Instagram on Thursday. READ: SA artist Nelson Makamo's painting on TIME magazine cover "This is more than just a collab... it’s more than just about me... and I can’t wait to share it all with you tomorrow," Moletsane said. The Nike AF1XKaraboPoppy collection will be available from 7 November at Nike.com. It’s almost here👟✍🏾! 7 November 2019 marks the day when years of blood, sweat and tears turn into the greatest moment of a person’s life and career. This is more than just a collab... it’s more than just about me... and I can’t wait to share it all with you tomorrow. Link in bio! — — — #KaraboPoppy #KaraboPoppyXNike #KaraboPoppyAirForce1 #KaraboByYou #Nike #AirForce1 #Illustration #Design #WomenInIllustration #AfricanAesthetic A post shared by  Karabo Poppy Moletsane (@karabo_poppy) on Nov 6, 2019 at 4:32am PST